SENATE BILL NO. 485
BY SENATOR EDMONDS
1 AN ACT
2 To amend and reenact R.S. 33:3078 and to enact R.S. 33:3077(8), relative to the city of St.
3 George; to provide relative to the allocation and exercise of certain municipal taxing
4 authority within the corporate limits of the city of St. George; to provide for
5 exclusive municipal administration of insurance premium taxes; to provide for the
6 levy of insurance premium tax; to provide for definitions; to provide for prospective
7 adjudication; to provide for an effective date; and to provide for related matters.
8 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
9 Section 1. R.S. 33:3078 is hereby amended and reenacted and R.S. 33:3077(8) is
10 hereby enacted to read as follows:
11 §3077. Definitions
12 Whenever used in this Part, unless a different meaning clearly appears in the
13 context, the following terms, whether used in the singular or plural, shall be given
14 the following interpretations:
15 * * *
16 (8) "Insurance premium tax" means a municipal license tax imposed on
17 insurers pursuant to R.S. 22:833 or any other applicable provision of law, based
18 upon premiums written on risks located within the taxing jurisdiction.
19 §3078. Continued levy of tax by East Baton Rouge Parish Insurance premium tax;
20 transition; authority to levy
21 A. Notwithstanding any law to the contrary, in the event the city of St.
22 George, as approved by the voters on October 12, 2019, is incorporated, the parish
23 may continue to levy and collect the parish tax within the corporate limits of the
24 municipality pursuant to an intergovernmental agreement between the parish and
25 municipality for the purpose of providing essential public services to, or funding
26 essential public services for, the citizens within St. George until the St. George
27 Transition District levies and collects a two percent sales and use tax, the
28 municipality levies and collects a two percent sales and use tax, the end of the
