1 quarter following the election to impose the municipal tax if the proposition is not
2 approved by the electorate, or twelve months after the incorporation becomes final,
3 whichever occurs first. beginning on January 1. 2027, the city of St. George shall
4 exclusively exercise all municipal authority to levy, collect, administer, and
5 enforce any insurance premium tax, as defined in R.S. 33:3077, on risk located
6 within the corporate limits of the city of St. George.
7 B. The city of Baton Rouge and the parish of East Baton Rouge,
8 including any component of the consolidated government, shall not levy, collect,
9 administer, or receive any insurance premium tax on risks located within the
10 corporate limits of the city of St. George.
11 C. Nothing in this Section shall be construed to authorize duplicative
12 taxation. An insurer shall be subject to only one local insurance premium tax
13 for a given risk and period.
14 D. The governing authority of the city of St. George and governing
15 authority of the parish of East Baton Rouge may enter into an
16 intergovernmental agreement solely for the purposes of records transfer,
17 closeout of prior records, and administrative cooperation, but not for the
18 continued collection of the insurance premium tax described in this Section by
19 the parish or consolidated government.
20 Section 2. The provisions of this Act shall become effective on January 1, 2027.
21 Section 3. The provisions of this Act shall apply prospectively only to premiums
22 attributable to periods beginning on and after January 1, 2027.
